"title": "4241: Garden of Eden, the",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4241: garden of eden, the",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The garden created by God and entrusted to the care of Adam and Eve.</p>\n<h2>The ``garden of the LORD''</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:8\">GEN 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:10\">GEN 13:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:9-Gen2:14\">GEN 2:9–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:3\">ISA 51:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:9\">EZK 31:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:18\">EZK 31:18</a> <em>Ancient Egypt is likened to Eden</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:35\">EZK 36:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:3\">JOL 2:3</a></p>\n<h2>The place of fellowship with God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8\">GEN 3:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Where God spoke to Adam</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:16-Gen2:18\">GEN 2:16–2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Where Adam was to work</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:15\">GEN 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:19\">GEN 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Where God made Eve and gave her to Adam</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:18\">GEN 2:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:20-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:20–2:24</a></p>\n<h3>Where Adam and Eve lived in innocence</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:25\">GEN 2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:7\">GEN 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:11\">GEN 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>Where God abundantly provided for Adam and Eve</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:9-Gen2:17\">GEN 2:9–2:17</a> <em>The trees of Eden are important.  They are both the evidence of God's love and one is the focus of Adam's test.</em></p>\n<h2>The paradise that humanity has lost</h2>\n<h3>Where Adam and Eve disobeyed God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6\">GEN 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:17\">GEN 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:7\">GEN 3:1–3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:11\">GEN 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>Where humanity came under God's curse</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:16–3:19</a></p>\n<h3>The place from which Adam and Eve were banished</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23\">GEN 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:22\">GEN 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:24\">GEN 3:24</a></p>\n<h2>The picture of God's blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:3\">ISA 51:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:11\">ISA 58:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:12\">JER 31:12</a></p>\n<h3>Where God first promised Satan's destruction</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:14-Gen3:15\">GEN 3:14–3:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Where God first provided a covering for sinners</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:21\">GEN 3:21</a></p>\n<h3>Eden as an anticipation of heaven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:43\">LUK 23:43</a></strong> <em>The word “paradise” (which means “park” or “walled garden”) clearly refers back to the idea of Eden.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:3\">2CO 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:4\">2CO 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1-Rev22:3\">REV 22:1–22:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:12-Ezek28:13\">EZK 28:12–28:13</a> <em>the former glory of the king of Tyre likened to that of Adam in the Garden of Eden</em></p>",
